Compute the saturated thickness

Source: R/utils.R
satthick.Rd

satthick() computes the saturated thickness of the aquifer of an aem object at the given x and y coordinates.

Usage

satthick(aem, x, y, as.grid = FALSE, ...)

Arguments

aem

aem object

x

numeric x coordinates to evaluate at

y

numeric y coordinates to evaluate at

as.grid

logical, should a matrix of dimensions c(length(y), length(x)) be returned? Defaults to FALSE.

...

additional arguments passed to heads() when aem$type = 'variable'.

Value

satthick() returns a vector of length(x) (equal to length(y)) with the saturated thicknesses at x and y. If as.grid = TRUE, a matrix of dimensions c(length(y), length(x)) described by marginal vectors x and y containing the saturated thicknesses at the grid points.

Details

If the aquifer is confined at x and y, the saturated thickness equals the aquifer thickness. For flow with variable saturated thickness, if the aquifer is unconfined at x and y, the saturated thickness it is calculated as the hydraulic head at x and y minus the aquifer base.

See also

flow(), state-variables()

Examples

uf <- uniformflow(100, 0.001, 0)
rf <- constant(-1000, 0, 11)
m <- aem(k = 10, top = 10, base = 0, n = 0.2, uf, rf, type = 'confined')

satthick(m, x = c(-200, 0, 200), y = 0) # confined
#> [1] 10 10 10
satthick(m, x = seq(-500, 500, length = 100),
         y = seq(-250, 250, length = 100), as.grid = TRUE)
